The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Nation Briefs

 Girls fingers chopped

 Bhagalpur, Dec. 23 (PTI): A Dalit girls fingers were allegedly chopped off by a farmer because she plucked spinach from his field in Bihars Bhagalpur district.

 The five fingers of 10-year-old Khushbu Kumaris right hand were cut by landowner Pankaj Rai at Bhavnathpur-Baijar village, police said. A case has been registered by the girls father.

 Poll card rap

 Chennai (PTI): Disciplinary action has been taken against erring officials who failed to destroy 1,633 electors photo identity cards, Erode district collector D. Karthikeyan has said. The Election Commission had instructed that the cards be destroyed but they were found in a dustbin on Friday.

 Air tease

 Chennai (PTI): A 27-year-old software engineer, who arrived here by an Emirates flight from Dubai, was arrested for misbehaving with an air hostess. The engineer was remanded in 15 days judicial custody.

 Kalam on IITs

 Mumbai (PTI): President A.P.J. Abdul Kalam has said there was almost no value addition to students by the IITs. They (the students) are the best children. Wherever you put them they will do very well. But value addition by an IIT is very low to the students it admits, he said.

 RTI on call

 Patna (PTI): Bihar will soon become the first state where information under the Right to Information Act will be available by making a phone call.

 A call centre will be set up for this.

 Zanskar ban 

 Jammu (PTI): Zanskar in Ladakh will soon be opened hist Youth Association lifting the seven-month ban on tourists on Thursday. The association took the decision in the hope that their demands would be met soon.

 AIDS week

 Chandigarh (PTI): The Chandigarh district administration will observe an AIDS Week in the thir symposia, seminars, painting competitions and cultural items will be organised.




